# Lokaa Project Cursor Rules

This project is a Skool-style SaaS app for discovering and joining creator-led communities. Auth is powered by Supabase. Routing is managed by React Router. All data operations must use Supabase MCP (especially for public space access and membership checks).


## GENERAL

- Always prefer Supabase MCP for all database reads/writes
- Use Supabase-generated types and RPC functions (never hardcode SQL in frontend)
- Avoid client-side filters when server-side filters can be applied via RPC
- Always optimize for fast-loading and mobile-first behavior
- Never use window.location.href — always use React Router's `navigate()` unless explicitly routing away from app

---

## ROUTING

- `/discover`: Public space listing page (for unauthenticated + authenticated users)
- `/:subdomain/about`: Public about page for any space — must NOT require auth
- `/space/:subdomain`: Main logged-in space interface. Requires access check
- Clicking on a space card must **always open `/:subdomain/about` in a new tab**, even if user is logged in

---

## COMPONENTS

### SpaceAboutPage.tsx
- Uses `about_page_get_space` RPC (public) to fetch space data
- No redirects or auth required to view
- Match layout to Skool’s About page (gallery, testimonials, pricing, creator, join button)
- If space not found: Show custom "Space Not Found" page, do not crash

### Discover.tsx
- Space cards must link to `/:subdomain/about` and open in a new tab
- OnClick: Save `lastViewedSpace` in localStorage (subdomain, id, name)
- Never trigger space login from space card click
- Fetch public spaces via `get_public_spaces` RPC using Supabase MCP
- Show loading spinner if spaces are still loading

---

## AUTH HANDLING

- After login, if user has a space, redirect them to `/space/:subdomain`
- Never override routing logic when on `/create-space`, `/login`, or `/signup`
- Use `redirectToSpace()` util from `spaceRedirect.ts` for all routing logic
- Always check both `owner_id` and `space_access` for access control

---

## PERFORMANCE

- All space cards, dropdowns, and routes must load in < 300ms
- Use `swr` or `react-query` caching where appropriate
- Debounce heavy queries and avoid double fetching

---

## DEBUGGING UTILITIES

- Access checks should be logged in browser console (i.e. "User has access via membership")
- Add temporary `window.debugSpaceAccess()` to manually test access if needed
